# install on windows

## env

1. install nodejs
2. install postgresql
    2.1. set {your_pg_dir}/bin to 'path' environment
    2.2. set {your_pg_dir}/data to PGDATA environment 
    2.3. prepare bootstrap:
        2.3.1 run {your_pg_dir}/bin/initdb.exe to create configs / datas etc in your PGDATA directory
        2.3.2 run {your_pg_dir}/bin/createuser.exe {username} -d, to create user without password login, and give it permission to create database
        2.3.3 use pgadmin4/psql or other tools login database via user {username} and database {postgres}
        2.3.4 create application database {your_app_db}
        2.3.5 create application tables in {your_app_db}

## projects

1. create your app directory tree like:
    - Project-A
      - backend
        - src
        - other (configs file by python / go / java etc.)
        - .ci   (ci flow files, like jenkins / dockers etc.)
      - frontend

2. run this commands to install Svelte:
```shell
   cd Project-A/frontend
   npm config set registry https://registry.npmmirror.com
   npm create svelte@latest myapp
   cd myapp
   npm install
```

3. run this commands to install Prisma(frontend db access):
```shell
   npm install prisma --save-dev
   npx prisma init
```

4. run this commands to install Skeleton(svelte css componments)
```shell
    npm i @skeletonlabs/skeleton --save-dev
    npx svelte-add@latest tailwindcss
    npm install
```
replace tailwind.config.cjs with
```javascript
/** @type {import('tailwindcss').Config} */
module.exports = {
	// 1. Apply the dark mode class setting:
	darkMode: 'class',
	content: [
		'./src/**/*.{html,js,svelte,ts}',
		// 2. Append the path for the Skeleton NPM package and files:
		require('path').join(require.resolve(
			'@skeletonlabs/skeleton'),
			'../**/*.{html,js,svelte,ts}'
		)
	],
	theme: {
		extend: {},
	},
	plugins: [
		// 3. Append the Skeleton plugin to the end of this list
		...require('@skeletonlabs/skeleton/tailwind/skeleton.cjs')()
	]
}
```
create src/routes/+layout.svelte with below
```javascript
<script>
  // Your selected Skeleton theme:
  import '@skeletonlabs/skeleton/themes/theme-skeleton.css';

  // This contains the bulk of Skeletons required styles:
  import '@skeletonlabs/skeleton/styles/all.css';

  // Finally, your application's global stylesheet (sometimes labeled 'app.css')
  import '../app.postcss';
</script>

<slot />

```

5. add this to package.json to use other tools via npm:
```json
  "scripts": {
    "pgstart": "pg_ctl start",
    "pgstop": "pg_ctl stop",
    "prsima_prepared": "npx prisma db pull && npx prisma generate",
  }
```

6. run this commands to open git supports:
```shell
   git init
   git add .
   git commit -m "first commit"
   git push --set-upstream https://your_git_repo.git master
```
   